      "writtenOn": "2026-03-10T02:08:37Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "@gunnar@gmills.xyz\nBecause the object path name has no enforced format. \nFor example,Function0, Function_0, and PCIeFunc0 all represent function 0 but require different parsing rules. Reading the FunctionNumber property avoids guessing — it is the value the interface guarantees.\nI could also just extract trailing digits from the path segment as a simpler alternative. \nWhich approach do you prefer?",
