      "writtenOn": "2026-03-10T16:21:54Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "\u003e Because the object path name has no enforced format.\nFor example,Function0, Function_0, and PCIeFunc0 all represent function 0\n\nBut you could have dimm0, dimm_0, and serverdimm0 all at /redfish/v1/Systems/{ComputerSystemId}/Memory/{MemoryId}\nWhy do we care in bmcweb? \nWe are just translating D-Bus to Redfish in bmcweb. (oversimplifying..)\nWhy are extracting the trailing digit?",
