      "writtenOn": "2026-03-10T05:56:52Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Thanks for pointing to getChassisContainedBy(). I can see the pattern — use getAssociatedSubTreePaths, then call object_path(p).filename() to get the name and build the Redfish URL directly.\n\n  In the chassis case, filename() (e.g. HGX_Chassis) is used as-is for the Id and URL, since Redfish Id is just a string with no format constraint.\n\nFor PCIeFunction, if we follow the same approach, the URL would become /PCIeDevices/GPU_SXM_1/PCIeFunctions/Function0 instead of /PCIeDevices/GPU_SXM_1/PCIeFunctions/0. \nThe Redfish spec doesn\u0027t require the URL segment to be a number — only FunctionId (a separate integer property) needs to carry the actual PCIe function number, which we can still extract from the filename.\n\nWould you prefer to go with this approach (use filename() directly as the Id), or keep the numeric-only URL (which requires extracting trailing digits from the filename)?",
      "parentUuid": "2011aa7c_a1d85b15",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 795,
        "startChar": 27,
