      "writtenOn": "2026-03-10T07:13:02Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "The numeric URL (/PCIeFunctions/0) was a requirement of the old interface, where properties were named Function0FunctionType, Function1FunctionType, etc. — the number in the URL was needed to construct the correct property name to look up.\n\nSince I\u0027m now switching to the new xyz.openbmc_project.Inventory.Item.PCIeFunction interface (one object per function), there\u0027s no longer a need to carry a numeric ID in the URL. So I\u0027d like to follow the same pattern as getChassisContainedBy() and use the object path filename directly as the Redfish Id (e.g. /PCIeFunctions/Function0).\n\nThe Redfish spec only requires Id to be a unique string — it doesn\u0027t need to be numeric. The integer FunctionId property can still be populated separately by extracting the trailing digits from the filename.",
      "parentUuid": "cb9fbf66_b5bcbf81",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 795,
        "startChar": 27,
